'''''Jedi Quest: Path to Truth''''' is the introductory novel for the [[Star Wars: Jedi Quest (novel series)|Jedi Quest]] series chronicling the adventures of [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] and his master, [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]], between [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']] and [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']].

The story was also told in [[Star Wars: Jedi Quest (comic series)|comic form]].

==Publisher's summary==
<div align="center">'''CHOSEN TO RISE.'''<br />'''DESTINED TO FALL.'''</div>

''Anakin Skywalker is no longer a boy, but not yet a man. Almost thirteen, he has begun to travel on the path that will lead him to glory&hellip;and infamy.''

''In the mysterious caves of Ilum, Anakin must create his lightsaber after confronting the demons of his past&mdash;and his future. Once the lightsaber is completed, Anakin joins his Master, Obi-Wan Kenobi, on a mission that will cut to the heart of his fear, anger, and power.''

''When Anakin was a young slave on Tatooine, everyone lived in terror of a creature named Krayn, who kidnapped slaves for his own profit&mdash;and killed anyone who got in his way. Now Krayn's evil has grown to a dangerous degree, threatening peace and safe passage throughout the galaxy''.

''Anakin and Obi-Wan must stop Krayn. But can Obi-Wan also stop Anakin from seeking vengeance against an old enemy?''

''The path to truth is a clear one.''

''Anakin's path is not.''

==Plot summary==
At age thirteen, [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] climbs the [[Water/Legends|icy]] [[Mountain/Legends|cliffs]] of [[Ilum/Legends|Ilum]] to seek out the [[Lightsaber crystal/Legends|crystal]] necessary to construct his own [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]]. Anakin stares down [[Force vision/Legends|visions]] of his worst fears, including images of his [[Parent/Legends|mother]] imperiled and the evil [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]], [[Darth Maul/Legends|Darth Maul]]. Returning with a lightsaber of his own, Anakin is soon given a new assignment with his [[Jedi Master/Legends|Master]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]]: protecting a [[Starship/Legends|starship]] from the [[Pirate/Legends|pirate]] [[Krayn]]. Anakin has long known of Krayn, for the dreadful raider terrorized the [[Slave Quarters Row/Legends|Mos Espa Slave Quarters]] in Anakin’s youth. 

Infiltrating Krayn’s [[Spice/Legends|spice]]-processing operation on [[Nar Shaddaa/Legends|Nar Shaada]], Anakin makes it his personal mission to confront and destroy Krayn. He finds out that Krayn’s [[Lieutenant/Legends|lieutenant]], Zora, is actually [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Siri Tachi/Legends|Siri Tachi]] operating deep undercover. Obi-Wan likewise surreptitiously enters Krayn’s compound, posing as a [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]]. The Jedi work together to liberate the [[Slavery/Legends|enslaved]] workers, and Anakin [[Death/Legends|kills]] Krayn with [[Anakin Skywalker's first lightsaber/Legends|his lightsaber]].

